# English-only language policy

- Use **English** for everything in this project: code identifiers, comments/docstrings, documentation, logs, and user-facing text.
- Avoid Spanish (or any other non-English language) in filenames, commit messages, PR/issue text, and in-app copy.

## Exceptions (rare)

- Proper nouns (e.g., product/brand names), quoted external material, or pasted user-provided content.
- If localization is required: keep **source strings in English** and put other languages only in dedicated i18n/locale files (e.g., `locales/es.json`).

## Examples

```ts
// ❌ BAD (Spanish)
// Validar si el usuario existe
function validarUsuario() {}

// ✅ GOOD (English)
// Validate whether the user exists
function validateUser() {}
```
